			<div class="recipe-card-ingredients">
            			
			<h3 class="ingredients-title">Ingredients</h3>
            			<ul class="ingredients-list layout-1-column"><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-686fff7684605" class="ingredient-item ingredient-item-group"><strong class="ingredient-item-group-title">For the Cake:</strong></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-686fff7684606" class="ingredient-item"><span class="tick-circle"></span><p class="ingredient-item-name is-strikethrough-active"><span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-amount">1 1/2</span> <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-unit">cups</span>   <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span>  </p></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-686fff7684607" class="ingredient-item"><span class="tick-circle"></span><p class="ingredient-item-name is-strikethrough-active"><span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-unit">cup</span>   <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-name">granulated sugar</span>  </p></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-686fff7684608" class="ingredient-item"><span class="tick-circle"></span><p class="ingredient-item-name is-strikethrough-active"><span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span>   <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-name">baking soda</span>  </p></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-95" class="ingredient-item"><span class="tick-circle"></span><p class="ingredient-item-name is-strikethrough-active"><span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span>   <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-name">baking powder</span>  </p></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-122" class="ingredient-item"><span class="tick-circle"></span><p class="ingredient-item-name is-strikethrough-active"><span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span>   <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-name">salt</span>  </p></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-140" class="ingredient-item"><span class="tick-circle"></span><p class="ingredient-item-name is-strikethrough-active"><span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-unit">large</span>   <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-name">eggs, room temperature</span>  </p></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-171" class="ingredient-item"><span class="tick-circle"></span><p class="ingredient-item-name is-strikethrough-active"><span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-unit">cup</span>   <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-name">extra-virgin olive oil, mild and fruity</span>  </p></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-219" class="ingredient-item"><span class="tick-circle"></span><p class="ingredient-item-name is-strikethrough-active"><span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-unit">cup</span>   <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-name">whole milk, room temperature</span>  </p></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-256" class="ingredient-item"><span class="tick-circle"></span><p class="ingredient-item-name is-strikethrough-active">    <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-name">Zest of 2 lemons</span>  </p></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-273" class="ingredient-item"><span class="tick-circle"></span><p class="ingredient-item-name is-strikethrough-active"><span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-unit">cup</span>   <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-name">fresh lemon juice (from about 2 lemons)</span>  </p></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-321" class="ingredient-item"><span class="tick-circle"></span><p class="ingredient-item-name is-strikethrough-active"><span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span>   <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-name">pure vanilla extract</span>  </p></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-353" class="ingredient-item ingredient-item-group"><strong class="ingredient-item-group-title">For the Lemon Glaze:</strong></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-378" class="ingredient-item"><span class="tick-circle"></span><p class="ingredient-item-name is-strikethrough-active"><span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-unit">cup</span>   <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-name">powdered sugar, sifted</span>  </p></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-407" class="ingredient-item"><span class="tick-circle"></span><p class="ingredient-item-name is-strikethrough-active"><span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-amount">2-3</span>    <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-name">tablespoons fresh lemon juice</span>  </p></li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-item-441" class="ingredient-item"><span class="tick-circle"></span><p class="ingredient-item-name is-strikethrough-active"><span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span>   <span class="wpzoom-rcb-ingredient-name">finely grated lemon zest</span>  </p></li></ul>
					</div>
				
			
			<div class="recipe-card-directions">
			<h3 class="directions-title">Instructions</h3>
			<ul class="directions-list"><li id="wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-686fff7684609" class="direction-step">Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. Grease a 9-inch springform pan or line with parchment paper. Cover the bottom and sides of the pan with foil to prevent leaks.</li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-686fff768460a" class="direction-step">In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, and salt until well combined.</li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-686fff768460b" class="direction-step">Whisk the eggs in a separate large bowl. Slowly whisk in the olive oil until fully emulsified. Whisk in the milk, lemon zest, lemon juice, and vanilla.</li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-686fff768460c" class="direction-step">Gradually stir the dry mixture into the wet, folding gently with a spatula until no streaks of flour remain. The batter will be thin and glossy.</li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-1752170704735255" class="direction-step">Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Bake for 35-40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean or with a few moist crumbs.</li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-1752170704735256" class="direction-step">Let the cake cool in the pan for 15 minutes. Run a thin knife around the edge and release the springform ring. Cool the cake on a wire rack for another 30 minutes.</li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-1752170704735257" class="direction-step">In a small bowl, whisk the powdered sugar with lemon juice until smooth and pourable. Add more juice, a few drops at a time, if needed. Stir in the lemon zest.</li><li id="wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-1752170704735258" class="direction-step">Spoon the glaze over the cake, letting it drip down the sides. Allow the glaze to set for at least 15 minutes. Slice and enjoy.</li></ul>
		</div>
	
			
	
	
			<div class="recipe-card-notes">
			<h3 class="notes-title">Notes</h3>
			<ul class="recipe-card-notes-list"><li><strong>Topping options:</strong> Instead of lemon glaze, you can also top the cake with powdered sugar, fresh berries, and whipped cream. </li><li><strong>Add poppy seeds.</strong> Just add 1 tablespoon to the batter for a subtle crunch and extra texture.</li><li><strong>Go nuts: </strong>For a hint of nuttiness, swap 1/2 cup of the flour for almond flour. Add a teaspoon of almond extract to the batter.</li></ul>
		</div>
	
	
			<div class="recipe-card-nutrition">
			<h3 class="nutrition-title">Nutrition</h3>
			<ul class="recipe-card-nutrition-list"><li><strong>Total number of serves:</strong> <span class="wpzoon-rcb-nutrition-value">8</span></li><li><strong>Calories:</strong> <span class="wpzoon-rcb-nutrition-value">383kcal</span></li><li><strong>Fat:</strong> <span class="wpzoon-rcb-nutrition-value">22g</span></li><li><strong>Saturated Fat:</strong> <span class="wpzoon-rcb-nutrition-value">2g</span></li><li><strong>Cholesterol:</strong> <span class="wpzoon-rcb-nutrition-value">72mg</span></li><li><strong>Sodium:</strong> <span class="wpzoon-rcb-nutrition-value">263mg</span></li><li><strong>Potassium:</strong> <span class="wpzoon-rcb-nutrition-value">101mg</span></li><li><strong>Carbohydrates:</strong> <span class="wpzoon-rcb-nutrition-value">47g</span></li><li><strong>Fiber:</strong> <span class="wpzoon-rcb-nutrition-value">0g</span></li><li><strong>Sugar:</strong> <span class="wpzoon-rcb-nutrition-value">44g</span></li><li><strong>Protein:</strong> <span class="wpzoon-rcb-nutrition-value">4g</span></li><li><strong>Calcium:</strong> <span class="wpzoon-rcb-nutrition-value">46mg</span></li><li><strong>Iron:</strong> <span class="wpzoon-rcb-nutrition-value">1mg</span></li><li><strong>Vitamin D:</strong> <span class="wpzoon-rcb-nutrition-value">16mg</span></li></ul>
		</div>
	
	
	
			
		
		
		
		
				
    	
			<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https:\/\/schema.org","@type":"Recipe","name":"Lemon Olive Oil Cake","image":["https:\/\/insanelygoodrecipes.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Lemon-Olive-Oil-Cake-7.jpg","https:\/\/insanelygoodrecipes.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Lemon-Olive-Oil-Cake-7-500x500.jpg","https:\/\/insanelygoodrecipes.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Lemon-Olive-Oil-Cake-7-500x375.jpg","https:\/\/insanelygoodrecipes.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Lemon-Olive-Oil-Cake-7-480x270.jpg"],"description":"This Lemon Olive Oil Cake is sunshine in every slice. Moist, zesty, and effortlessly elegant, one bite will brighten your day.","keywords":"lemon cake, lemon olive oil cake, olive oil cake, lemon olive oil cake, lemon cake, olive oil cake","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kim - InsanelyGood"},"datePublished":"2025-07-18T18:06:41-04:00","prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT40M","totalTime":"PT55M","recipeCategory":["Dessert"],"recipeCuisine":["Mediterranean"],"recipeYield":["8","8 servings"],"nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"383 cal","carbohydrateContent":"47 g","cholesterolContent":"72 mg","fatContent":"22 g","proteinContent":"4 g","saturatedFatContent":"2 g","servingSize":"8 servings","sodiumContent":"263 mg","sugarContent":"44 g"},"recipeIngredient":["1 1\/2 cups all-purpose flour","1 cup granulated sugar","1\/2 teaspoon baking soda","1\/2 teaspoon baking powder","1\/2 teaspoon salt","3 large eggs, room temperature","3\/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil, mild and fruity","3\/4 cup whole milk, room temperature","Zest of 2 lemons","1\/4 cup fresh lemon juice (from about 2 lemons)","1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract","1 cup powdered sugar, sifted","2-3  tablespoons fresh lemon juice","1 teaspoon finely grated lemon zest"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. Grease a 9-inch springform pan or line with parchment paper. Cover the bottom and sides of the pan with foil to prevent leaks.","text":"Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. Grease a 9-inch springform pan or line with parchment paper. Cover the bottom and sides of the pan with foil to prevent leaks.","url":"https:\/\/insanelygoodrecipes.com\/lemon-olive-oil-cake\/#wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-686fff7684609","image":""},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, and salt until well combined.","text":"In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, and salt until well combined.","url":"https:\/\/insanelygoodrecipes.com\/lemon-olive-oil-cake\/#wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-686fff768460a","image":""},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Whisk the eggs in a separate large bowl. Slowly whisk in the olive oil until fully emulsified. Whisk in the milk, lemon zest, lemon juice, and vanilla.","text":"Whisk the eggs in a separate large bowl. Slowly whisk in the olive oil until fully emulsified. Whisk in the milk, lemon zest, lemon juice, and vanilla.","url":"https:\/\/insanelygoodrecipes.com\/lemon-olive-oil-cake\/#wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-686fff768460b","image":""},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Gradually stir the dry mixture into the wet, folding gently with a spatula until no streaks of flour remain. The batter will be thin and glossy.","text":"Gradually stir the dry mixture into the wet, folding gently with a spatula until no streaks of flour remain. The batter will be thin and glossy.","url":"https:\/\/insanelygoodrecipes.com\/lemon-olive-oil-cake\/#wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-686fff768460c","image":""},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Bake for 35-40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean or with a few moist crumbs.","text":"Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Bake for 35-40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean or with a few moist crumbs.","url":"https:\/\/insanelygoodrecipes.com\/lemon-olive-oil-cake\/#wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-1752170704735255","image":""},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Let the cake cool in the pan for 15 minutes. Run a thin knife around the edge and release the springform ring. Cool the cake on a wire rack for another 30 minutes.","text":"Let the cake cool in the pan for 15 minutes. Run a thin knife around the edge and release the springform ring. Cool the cake on a wire rack for another 30 minutes.","url":"https:\/\/insanelygoodrecipes.com\/lemon-olive-oil-cake\/#wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-1752170704735256","image":""},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"In a small bowl, whisk the powdered sugar with lemon juice until smooth and pourable. Add more juice, a few drops at a time, if needed. Stir in the lemon zest.","text":"In a small bowl, whisk the powdered sugar with lemon juice until smooth and pourable. Add more juice, a few drops at a time, if needed. Stir in the lemon zest.","url":"https:\/\/insanelygoodrecipes.com\/lemon-olive-oil-cake\/#wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-1752170704735257","image":""},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Spoon the glaze over the cake, letting it drip down the sides. Allow the glaze to set for at least 15 minutes. Slice and enjoy.","text":"Spoon the glaze over the cake, letting it drip down the sides. Allow the glaze to set for at least 15 minutes. Slice and enjoy.","url":"https:\/\/insanelygoodrecipes.com\/lemon-olive-oil-cake\/#wpzoom-rcb-direction-step-1752170704735258","image":""}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.8","ratingCount":6,"reviewCount":2},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Teri Kane"},"datePublished":"2025-11-20T14:03:03-05:00","reviewBody":"Delicious.  I added poppy seeds to the icing. Nice crunch"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":4},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"TARA"},"datePublished":"2026-04-17T13:44:35-04:00","reviewBody":"It sounds wonderful; I no longer have a springform pan.Lemons coast a fortune now, here.So Ill have to  sound out if I can afford real  lemons (or could I use LIMES&gt; ARE LIMES POSSIBLE?) THANK YOU."}]}</script>
